            . I am a watchman. On the 2d of July, between four and five o'clock in the morning, I stopped the prisoner in Lower Grosvenor-place, about one hundred yards from Mr. Clark's, with a bundle, containing a loaf of bread, some broken bread and butter, part of a leg of lamb dressed, and a frock-skirt; I asked where he got them - he said, he did not know.</p>
